CHECK:SPACING: spaces preferred around that '-' (ctx:VxV)
#148: FILE: kernel/hw_breakpoint.c:299:
+	for (i = HBP_NUM-1; i >= hbp_kernel_pos; i--) {
 	                ^

Whitespace style used in the kernel sources is described in kernel docs.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'hbp_kernel_pos == 0'
#195: FILE: kernel/hw_breakpoint.c:343:
+			if ((hbp_kernel_pos == 0) ||
+			    (hbp_user_refcount[hbp_kernel_pos - 1] != 0)) {

Parentheses are not required in the following cases:

  1. Function pointer uses::

      (foo->bar)();

    could be::

      foo->bar();

  2. Comparisons in if::

      if ((foo->bar) && (foo->baz))
      if ((foo == bar))

    could be::

      if (foo->bar && foo->baz)
      if (foo == bar)

  3. addressof/dereference single Lvalues::

      &(foo->bar)
      *(foo->bar)

    could be::

      &foo->bar
      *foo->bar

